<h1>Learn more about me</h1>
<h1>Hello, I am Elvis!</h1>
<p>Perhaps not the king of pop, but I love me some tenders. I will help 
you visualize, clean and explore tender data.</p><p>In this particular instance, we are focusing on defence tenders.</p>
<h2>What is Elvis?</h2>
<p>Elvis is visualization tool designed for displaying tender data as networks. In Elvis, you can filter the data, display them in a network visualization and clean the company names by merging the nodes that are the same company.</p>
<h2>Where does the data come from?</h2>
<p>Data in Defence Elvis come from two main 
sources:
<ul>
	<li><i>opentender.eu</i> - the most comprehensive collection of 
tenders around Europe from local and European tender data portals.</li>
<li><i>Manually collected</i> - tenders not present in the 
opentender.eu database, but collected from other online sources such as 
news articles</li></ul></p>

<h2>Table details</h2>
